@NODE news
@TITLE What is new in PicMenu V2.0 ?

What is new in PicMenu V2.0 ?
-----------------------------

  = Bug (PicMenu tries and tries to load prefs file and
    freez system) was erased.
  = Add anim keys (Left-Amiga-key) in menu.
  = PicMenu work in two mode:
    - with MagicMenu (recommended)
    - without MagicMenu (standard white background menu)
  = New prefs file format.
    - It's easy to add pictures to appmenu programs
    - You may change Workbench localization and
      PicMenu work correctly.
    - Users can't define size of anim pictograms.
      Now size is const=20 in MagicMenu Mode and
      const=24 in NO Magicmenu mode.
  = PicMenu doesn't require HD and interlaced 
    screen mode (but recommended)).
  = PicMenu V2.0 is faster then PicMenu V1.3

@ENDNODE



@NODE TD
@TITLE ToolDemon


A T T E N S I O N !!!

  PictureMenu does NOT work with ToolDemonem and RekeyIT
  ------------------------------------------------------

     I'm sorry. I wrote in PicMenu v1.3 guide you may add pictogram to
     ToolDemon menus. It isn't true. ToolDemon patches system functions and uses
     no standard procedures and dosn't recognize modyfied WB menu structure.
     So, I created new algoritm of PicMenu but it's seems that Workbench task
     generates own menu ... no standard (???). PictureMenu (v1.5 - internal version)
     which patch function SetMenuStrip() in intuition.library may add pictograms
     to all others programs without Workbench task (!!!???).

     So, if you want to use PictureMenu, install ToolMenager with docks to 
     run programs fast.


  If you use RekeyIT, you don't use PictureMenu but ...
Next version of PictureMenu (v2.1?) will add keyboard shortcut to WB menu like RekeyIT !!!
Let's wait for PictureMenu v2.1 (October '96)

@ENDNODE
